NOTE on pack count — 29/29 GREEN, not 30/30
---------------------------------------------
`marketplace/` has 30 top-level subdirectories, but only 29 of them are
actual packs. The 30th, `marketplace/Summary/`, is marketplace-listing
metadata (a per-pack `<name>.json` summary blurb plus preview `.png`
screenshots for the storefront UI) — it has no `mod_info.json` of its own.

PackSmokeCli's iteration rule (Step 1 of the brief) is "for each subdirectory
containing mod_info.json, invoke probe" — exactly the rule that correctly
excludes `Summary/` here. This is not a probe failure; `Summary/` was never
a pack to begin with. The brief's "30 shipped marketplace packs" framing
was an off-by-one over the raw subdirectory count, not a claim about
`Summary/`'s status.

Verified: none of the 29 real `mod_info.json` manifests declare an `assets`
array, so `PackLoaderProbe`'s asset-existence check never triggers in this
baseline — every pack that satisfies the three required manifest fields
(`name`, `version`, `min_cpd_version`) passes on the manifest-shape check
alone. All 29 do.

Slice 7 followup note: if a future pack adds an `assets` array (or if
`Summary/` is ever restructured to look pack-shaped), re-verify this
baseline — the current 29/29 GREEN result reflects the manifest-only
shape of the marketplace as of 2026-07-22.

